  "Has no time": [
   {
    "text": "A word in the ongoing tense of Hebrew or Aramaic does not alone tell us what time the action happened. This is like the English word \"running,\" which only describes an action, not when it happened. We require the context of the sentence to determine the time of the action.",
    "type": "text"
   }
  ],
  "In the past": [
   {
    "text": "The ongoing tense can be used in the past tense, for example הוא היה כותב, ",
    "type": "text"
   },
   {
    "type": "italics",
    "tokens": [
     {
      "text": "hu haya koisev",
      "type": "text"
     }
    ]
   },
   {
    "text": " meaning \"he used to write\" or \"he used to be writing.\" If you wanted to say \"he wrote,\" ie a one-time past event instead of an ongoing past event, you would just use the regular ",
    "type": "text"
   },
   {
    "text": "past tense",
    "type": "global",
    "tokens": [
     {
      "text": "past tense",
      "type": "text"
     }
    ],
    "targetSubtopic": "Past tense",
    "targetTopic": "Past tense",
    "enclosingTopic": "Ongoing tense",
    "enclosingSubtopic": "In the past"
   },
   {
    "text": ", and not the \"past-tense version\" of the ongoing tense.",
    "type": "text"
   }
  ],
  "In the present": [
   {
    "text": "The ongoing tense can be used in the present tense by adding a noun before the verb, for example, הוא כותב, ",
    "type": "text"
   },
   {
    "type": "italics",
    "tokens": [
     {
      "text": "hu koisev",
      "type": "text"
     }
    ]
   },
   {
    "text": ", meaning \"he is writing\" or \"he writes.\"",
    "type": "text"
   }
  ],
  "In the future": [
   {
    "text": "The ongoing tense can be used in the future tense, for example, הוא יהיה כותב, ",
